Commentary Text: Shreyas Gopal to Pant, out Bowled!! Oh dear! That's so soft, Pant looks gutted, stays in the crease for a long while, head down and then begins the long walk to the pavilion. This was a wide full-toss, was there to be put away, but Pant perhaps got a tad too greedy, went for power rather than placement - went too hard on the drive, lost his shape, gets an inside edge which bounced onto the off-stump. Pooran yelps in delight, Shreyas has relief on the face and Ian Bishop informs that this is the first time that Pant has been dismissed by a spinner in #IPL2022. Pant b Shreyas Gopal 26(16) [4s-1 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Thakur to Pooran, out Caught by Powell!! There's the killer blow! DC will be relieved. A high full toss from Shardul Thakur, Pooran walks forward and across to heave it away and miscues. The ball goes a long way up in the air and Powell gobbles it up after moving to his left from long-on. The TV umpire had to check if it was a fair delivery. The ball was dipping on the batter and Pooran was outside his crease as well. So, the third umpire ruled in favour of the fielding side. End of a supeb, fighting knock from Pooran. Pooran c Powell b Thakur 62(34) [4s-2 6s-6]
